[30;1m7 | [0m[35mHow to update a subset of weights?[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35m==================================[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35mIf you want to update only a subset of a weight matrix (such as[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35msome rows or some columns) that are used in the forward propagation[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35mof each iteration, then the cost function should be defined in a way[0m

[30;1m15 | [0m[35mPyTensor. Under the hood, this function will perform some processing on its[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35minputs and instantiate the `Scan` `Op` class which implements the looping[0m
[30;1m17 | [0m[35mmechanism. It achieves this by compiling its own PyTensor function representing[0m
[30;1m18 | [0m[35mthe computation to be done at every iteration of the loop and calling it as[0m
[30;1m19 | [0m[35mmany times as necessary.[0m

[30;1m266 | [0m[35m============================[0m
[30;1m267 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m268 | [0m[35mBecause of the complexity involved in dealing with `Scan`, a large number of[0m
[30;1m269 | [0m[35mhelper classes and functions have been developed over time to implement[0m
[30;1m270 | [0m[35moperations commonly needed when dealing with the `Scan`\ `Op`. The `Scan`\ `Op`[0m
[30;1m271 | [0m[35mitself defines a large number of them and others can be found in the file[0m
[30;1m272 | [0m[35m``utils.py``. This sections aims to point out the most useful ones sorted[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1509[0m[34m of [0m[33m2471[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/pytensor-2.30.3/doc/extending/scan.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(apt|apt\-get|aria2c|arp|ash|awk|base64|bash|bpftrace|busybox|cat|chmod|chown|cp|cpan|cpulimit|crontab|csh|curl|cut|dash|dd|diff|dmesg|dmsetup|dnf|docker|dpkg|easy_install|ed|emacs|env|expand|expect|facter|find|finger|flock|fmt|ftp|gawk|gdb|gimp|git|grep|head|iftop|ionice|ip|irb|jjs|journalctl|jrunscript|ksh|ld\.so|ldconfig|logsave|ltrace|lua|mail|mawk|mount|mtr|mv|mysql|nano|nawk|nc|nice|nl|nmap|node|od|openssl|perl|pg|php|pic|pico|pip|puppet|readelf|red|rlogin|rlwrap|rpm|rpmquery|rsync|ruby|run\-mailcap|run\-parts|rvim|scp|screen|script|sed|service|setarch|sftp|shuf|smbclient|socat|sort|sqlite3|ssh|start\-stop\-daemon|stdbuf|strace|systemctl|tail|tar|taskset|tclsh|tcpdump|tee|telnet|tftp|time|timeout|tmux|top|ul|unexpand|uniq|unshare|vi|vim|watch|wget|whois|wish|xargs|xxd|yum|zsh|zypper)\s[0m
[30;1m247 | [0m[35mtogether comes from the possibility of both original `Scan`\ `Op`\s having some[0m
[30;1m248 | [0m[35mcomputation in common. In such a setting, this computation ends up being done[0m
[30;1m249 | [0m[35mtwice. The fused `Scan`\s, however, would only need to do it once and could[0m
[30;1m250 | [0m[35mtherefore be more computationally efficient. Also, since every `Scan` node[0m
[30;1m251 | [0m[35minvolves a certain overhead, at runtime, reducing the number of `Scan` nodes in[0m
[30;1m252 | [0m[35mthe graph can improve performance.[0m
[30;1m253 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m254 | [0m[35m[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1510[0m[34m of [0m[33m2471[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m

[30;1m242 | [0m[35m`ScanMerge`[0m
[30;1m243 | [0m[35m-----------[0m
[30;1m244 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m245 | [0m[35mThis rewrite attempts to fuse distinct `Scan` nodes into a single `Scan` node[0m
[30;1m246 | [0m[35mthat performs all the computation. The main advantage of merging `Scan` nodes[0m
[30;1m247 | [0m[35mtogether comes from the possibility of both original `Scan`\ `Op`\s having some[0m
[30;1m248 | [0m[35mcomputation in common. In such a setting, this computation ends up being done[0m
[30;1m249 | [0m[35mtwice. The fused `Scan`\s, however, would only need to do it once and could[0m

[30;1m51 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m52 | [0m[35mIf C code is necessary, the flag[0m
[30;1m53 | [0m[35m``optimizer=fast_compile`` can be used instead. It instructs PyTensor to[0m
[30;1m54 | [0m[35mskip time consuming rewrites but still generate C code.[0m
[30;1m55 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m56 | [0m[35mSimilarly using the flag ``optimizer_excluding=inplace`` will speed up[0m
[30;1m57 | [0m[35mcompilation by preventing rewrites that replace operations with a[0m

[30;1m44 | [0m[35mFaster PyTensor Function Compilation[0m
[30;1m45 | [0m[35m------------------------------------[0m
[30;1m46 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m47 | [0m[35mPyTensor function compilation can be time consuming. It can be sped up by setting[0m
[30;1m48 | [0m[35mthe flag ``mode=FAST_COMPILE`` which instructs PyTensor to skip most[0m
[30;1m49 | [0m[35mrewrites and disables the generation of any c/cuda code. This is useful[0m
[30;1m50 | [0m[35mfor quickly testing a simple idea.[0m

[30;1m6 | [0m[35m=======================================[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35mThis tutorial covers how to extend PyTensor with an :class:`Op` that offers a C[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35mimplementation.  This tutorial is aimed at individuals who already know how to[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35mextend PyTensor (see tutorial :ref:`creating_an_op`) by adding a new :class:`Op`[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35mwith a Python implementation and will only cover the additional knowledge[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35mrequired to also produce :class:`Op`\s with C implementations.[0m

[30;1m221 | [0m[35m   By default when rewrites are enabled, we remove during[0m
[30;1m222 | [0m[35m   function compilation :class:`Apply` nodes whose inputs are all constants.[0m

[30;1m226 | [0m[35m   function call, make do_constant_folding return False.[0m

[30;1m202 | [0m[35mOpFromGraph nodes[0m
[30;1m203 | [0m[35m-----------------[0m
[30;1m204 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m205 | [0m[35mAn ``OpFromGraph`` node defines a new operation, which can be called with[0m
[30;1m206 | [0m[35mdifferent inputs at different places in the compute graph. Each ``OpFromGraph``[0m
[30;1m207 | [0m[35mnode defines a nested graph, which will be visualized accordingly by ``d3viz``.[0m
[30;1m208 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m1048 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m1049 | [0m[35m* Rewrites are organized in a hierarchy. At the top level, there[0m

[30;1m554 | [0m[35m========================================[0m
[30;1m555 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m556 | [0m[35mPyTensor exports a symbol called :obj:`optdb` which acts as a sort of ordered[0m
[30;1m557 | [0m[35mdatabase of rewrites. When a new rewrite is constructed, it must be inserted at[0m
[30;1m558 | [0m[35mthe proper place in the database in order for it to be deployed during function[0m
[30;1m559 | [0m[35mcompilation.[0m

[30;1m31 | [0m[35mSome graph rewriters navigate the computation graph in a particular fashion[0m
[30;1m32 | [0m[35m(e.g. in topological order, reverse-topological order, random order, etc.) and[0m
[30;1m33 | [0m[35mapply one or more node rewriters at each step.  :class:`WalkingGraphRewriter` is[0m
[30;1m34 | [0m[35mone such example.[0m
[30;1m35 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m36 | [0m[35mRewriters that are holistic, meaning that they must take into[0m

[30;1m1050 | [0m[35m  is a :class:`SequentialGraphRewriter`. It contains other rewriters,[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1911[0m[34m of [0m[33m2471[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m138 | [0m[35mwant to use the method it publishes instead of the call to toposort)[0m
[30;1m139 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m140 | [0m[35mThen, in :meth:`GraphRewriter.apply` we do the actual job of simplification. We start by[0m
[30;1m141 | [0m[35miterating through the graph in topological order. For each node[0m
[30;1m142 | [0m[35mencountered, we check if it's a ``div`` node. If not, we have nothing[0m
[30;1m143 | [0m[35mto do here. If so, we put in ``x``, ``y`` and ``z`` the numerator,[0m
[30;1m144 | [0m[35mdenominator and quotient (output) of the division.[0m
[30;1m145 | [0m[35mThe simplification only occurs when the numerator is a multiplication,[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1912[0m[34m of [0m[33m2471[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m

[30;1m110 | [0m[35m           fgraph.attach_feature(ReplaceValidate())[0m

[30;1m328 | [0m[35m        # when we look for it, we will find it in the subclass.  We[0m
[30;1m329 | [0m[35m        # don't want that, so we check the class.  When we add one, we[0m
[30;1m330 | [0m[35m        # add one only to the current class, so all is working[0m
[30;1m331 | [0m[35m        # correctly.[0m

[30;1m106 | [0m[35m    Op[0m
[30;1m107 | [0m[35m        The ``.op`` of an :term:`Apply`, together with its symbolic inputs[0m
[30;1m108 | [0m[35m        fully determines what kind of computation will be carried out for that[0m
[30;1m109 | [0m[35m        :class:`Apply` at run-time.  Mathematical functions such as addition[0m
[30;1m110 | [0m[35m        (i.e. :func:`pytensor.tensor.add`) and indexing ``x[i]`` are :class:`Op`\s[0m
[30;1m111 | [0m[35m        in PyTensor.  Much of the library documentation is devoted to describing[0m

[30;1m162 | [0m[35m    View[0m
[30;1m163 | [0m[35m        Some tensor :class:`Op`\s (such as :class:`Subtensor` and :class:`DimShuffle`) can be comput[0m
[30;1m164 | [0m[35m        constant time by simply re-indexing their inputs.   The outputs of[0m
[30;1m165 | [0m[35m        such :class:`Op`\s are views because their[0m
[30;1m166 | [0m[35m        storage might be aliased to the storage of other variables (the inputs[0m
[30;1m167 | [0m[35m        of the :class:`Apply`).  It is important for PyTensor to know which :class:`Variable`\s are[0m
